00:32:51.530 --> 00:32:54.215
So you can see the code there.

00:32:54.215 --> 00:32:56.340
So again, we just want to
make it easy for anybody.

00:32:56.340 --> 00:32:58.173
So again, we worked
with the micro:bit team,

00:32:58.173 --> 00:33:01.010
but we wanted to let anybody who
is making new types of hardware

00:33:01.010 --> 00:33:02.060
be able to extend it.

00:33:02.060 --> 00:33:03.990
So we're working with
the LEGO company,

00:33:03.990 --> 00:33:06.280
so as they add
new robotics kits,

00:33:06.280 --> 00:33:09.680
they'll be using Scratch and
just having extensions to--

00:33:09.680 --> 00:33:12.617
they'll both use the Scratch
blocks in their own apps,

00:33:12.617 --> 00:33:14.450
but also will have
extensions in the Scratch

00:33:14.450 --> 00:33:17.810
3.0, where you can control
your LEGO robotics.

00:33:17.810 --> 00:33:21.020
We're also working on some of
our own hardware extensions.

00:33:21.020 --> 00:33:22.517
So this is one.

